# Section 5 — Learning Reflection

when i was implementing RenderEngine, HTML Parser, and Seen Storage i learned

* Browser rendering is different from simple HTTP fetching because JavaScript execution changes the final DOM content.
* CDP communication requires handling asynchronous events and command responses separately.
* HTML parsing requires more than searching for strings because real websites contain different attribute formats and relative URL structures.
* KMP string matching can be used as a lightweight searching mechanism inside the parser.
* URL extraction and URL scheduling should remain separate responsibilities.
* A crawler must prevent duplicate crawling, which requires a dedicated storage layer.
* Wrapper classes like SeenStorage improve modularity because the crawler does not directly depend on the underlying Set implementation.
* Custom data structures can be integrated into larger systems instead of relying on STL containers.

The biggest learning from today's development was understanding how individual crawler modules connect together. Fetching, rendering, parsing, validation, normalization, and duplicate prevention are separate responsibilities that together form a scalable crawler structure.

